## When To Use This

**✅ Use a dOSPO when your ecosystem has:**

- Multiple independent entities (protocol orgs, foundations, DAOs, commercial ventures) that all depend on the same shared open source infrastructure
- Critical infrastructure maintained by individuals with no formal obligation, compensation, or succession plan
- Security incidents that require rapid cross-team coordination with no clear authority to organize response
- Treasury funds but no systematic way to fund maintenance vs. new features
- Duplicated effort across projects with no portfolio-level visibility

**❌ Do not use a dOSPO when:**

- The ecosystem is small and experimental (< a handful of active projects)
- Dependency failures are localized and recoverable
- Authority is already legitimately centralized
- Coordination cost exceeds failure cost
- You are looking for a governance body that sets direction — that is the community's job, not the dOSPO's

