## Core Functions

The dOSPO operator performs coordination that the ecosystem cannot reliably perform through ad hoc alignment:

| Function | Description |
|---|---|
| **Intake & triage** | Single intake surface for ecosystem-wide proposals and issues |
| **Portfolio visibility** | Dependency map, project health dashboards, builder profiles |
| **Funding coordination** | Administer lifecycle-aligned funding programs approved by governance |
| **Cross-project alignment** | Facilitate coordination where dependencies overlap |
| **Security coordination** | Organize incident response per Security Domain policy |
| **Transparency reporting** | Quarterly outcomes reports tied to mandate criteria |
| **Developer community stewardship** | Onboarding paths, contribution frameworks, cross-project visibility |

**The operator does not:**
- Set ecosystem roadmaps
- Allocate funds outside governance-approved programs
- Own repositories or IP
- Replace maintainers outside a published governance process
- Operate programs without sunset clauses

→ Full non-powers list: [`NON-POWERS.md`](NON-POWERS.md)

